      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "OBAT Helpers excels in financial health and transparency. They maintain <cite id=\"11\">5.7 months of operating reserves</cite>, which provides a critical safety net for their international programs. Their commitment to transparency is reflected in their <cite id=\"13\">Candid Platinum Seal</cite> and a <cite id=\"14\">perfect 100/100 score in Culture & Leadership</cite> from Charity Navigator. This governance strength is supported by a <cite id=\"12\">fully independent board</cite> that oversees a diverse range of services from W.A.S.H. initiatives to emergency relief."
      ],
      "summary": "OBAT Helpers Inc. is a dedicated humanitarian organization that has worked since <cite id=\"1\">its founding in 2004</cite> to empower displaced and marginalized communities in Bangladesh. The organization focuses on breaking the cycle of poverty through <cite id=\"2\">education, healthcare, and youth development</cite>. OBAT maintains a strong financial profile, evidenced by an <cite id=\"3\">overall score of 90.90.33333333333333/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>. While the organization manages <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $2,184,558</cite>, it operates with high efficiency, maintaining a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 82.1%</cite> and an impressive fundraising efficiency of <cite id=\"6\">$0.06 spent to raise every $1</cite>. Their work is deeply rooted in direct service delivery, operating <cite id=\"7\">50 educational and training projects</cite> and <cite id=\"8\">3 health clinics</cite> to serve those in need. For Muslim donors, OBAT provides a <cite id=\"9\">verified zakat-eligible platform</cite> that directs funds toward the poor and needy (fuqara and masakin) within refugee and internally displaced populations. Despite a <cite id=\"10\">27% revenue decline in the most recent fiscal year</cite>, the charity remains resilient with <cite id=\"11\">5.7 months of working capital</cite> in reserve, ensuring stability for its ongoing international operations.",
